@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About — Dez Reunion Events</PageTitle>

<section class="section page-hero">
    <div class="container text-center">
        <span class="eyebrow">Our Story</span>
        <h1 class="section-title">About Dez Reunion Events</h1>
        <p class="section-subtitle">A community built one dance floor at a time.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section" style="padding-top:0">
    <div class="container section-narrow">
        <h2>Where It Started</h2>
        <p>
            Dez Reunion Events began with a simple idea — that the people who once shared classrooms, streets and
            summers deserve a reason to come back together. What started as a small gathering of old friends
            has grown into a community-wide celebration, bringing people back to the dance floor season after season.
        </p>
        <p>
            Today, Dez Reunion Events hosts socials, galas and reunions throughout the year, each one designed to feel
            less like an event and more like coming home.
        </p>

        <hr class="divider-gradient" style="margin: 2.5rem auto" />

        <h2>Our Mission</h2>
        <p>
            To create spaces where community, culture and celebration meet — where every reunion strengthens
            the bonds that distance and time try to loosen. We exist to make reconnecting easy, joyful, and
            something to look forward to every year.
        </p>

        <hr class="divider-gradient" style="margin: 2.5rem auto" />

        <h2>Community Guidelines</h2>
        <p>Every Dez Reunion Events gathering is built on a few simple principles we ask all guests to honor:</p>
        <ul class="guidelines-list">
            <li>
                <strong>Respect Everyone</strong>
                <span>Treat every guest, staff member and performer with kindness and respect, regardless of background.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Inclusivity First</strong>
                <span>Dez Reunion Events is a space for everyone in our community — come as you are.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Zero Tolerance for Harassment</strong>
                <span>Harassment, discrimination or aggressive behaviour of any kind will result in removal from the event.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Safety Comes First</strong>
                <span>Follow venue safety guidance, drink responsibly, and look out for one another.</span>
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong>Respect the Venue</strong>
                <span>Help us take care of the spaces that host us so we're always welcome back.</span>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <div class="text-center" style="margin-top:2.5rem">
            <a href="/events" class="btn btn-primary">See Our Upcoming Events</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
